1 WHEREAS, Other horrific genocides have occurred throughout
2 history in places such as Armenia, Cambodia, Darfur, Guatemala
3 and Rwanda; and
4 WHEREAS, In 2005, the United Nations General Assembly
5 designated January 27, which is the anniversary of the liberation of
6 Auschwitz-Birkenau, as International Holocaust Remembrance Day
7 to commemorate the victims of the Holocaust and to promote
8 education about the Holocaust throughout the world; and
9 WHEREAS, A survey released in 2024 by the Governor’s
10 Advisory Council on Education Relating to the Holocaust revealed a
11 significant lack of knowledge about the Holocaust and other
12 genocides among Nevadans, particularly the younger generation;
13 and
14 WHEREAS, Assembly Bill No. 231 was enacted during the 81st
15 (2021) Session of the Nevada Legislature to direct efforts to
16 improve the curricula of courses provided to pupils in Nevada about
17 the Holocaust and other genocides as well as to increase the
18 classroom resources and professional development courses available
19 to educators on genocide education; and
20 WHEREAS, The annual observance of International Holocaust
21 Remembrance Day in Nevada will preserve the memory of the
22 victims of the Holocaust and other genocides and promote public
23 knowledge of these atrocities as well as serve as a reminder for
24 continued vigilance against hatred, persecution and tyranny to
25 prevent their reoccurrence; now, therefore,
26
27 THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
28 SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
29
30 Section 1. Chapter 236 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
31 thereto a new section to read as follows:
32 1. January 27 of each year is designated as “International
33 Holocaust Remembrance Day” in the State of Nevada.
34 2. The Governor shall issue annually a proclamation
35 encouraging the observance of “International Holocaust
36 Remembrance Day.” The proclamation must, without limitation,
37 call upon the news media, state and local officers, public schools
38 and other public and private entities to bring to the attention of the
39 people in the State of Nevada information about the Holocaust
40 and other genocides throughout history and the importance of
41 remembering the victims of the Holocaust and other genocides.
